    rationale: "A family member's verbal report of patient preferences is important collateral history but is not legally equivalent to a formal advance directive, POLST (Physician Orders for Life-Sustaining Treatment), or MOLST document. The appropriate action is to urgently search the medical record for a formal document while simultaneously preparing for intubation. If no formal document exists and the patient is in immediate danger, the default is to provide life-sustaining treatment until the situation is clarified. Proceeding without any consideration of the family's report ignores important clinical information. Accepting a verbal report as legally binding without documentation is inappropriate. Ethics committee consultation is not feasible in an acute emergency.",
